				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Bards<a name="20109"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 04 6:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Perhaps I have been playing too long to hold to the game as it is today.  Back in the day when bards seemed different.  I see names poping up out of no where.  Level 65 bard lfg.  At first there is a pause to try to recall this name, and alas there is no history.  A little later, I hear chat about this bard, who can't do anything except mez, or pulls 5 mobs at once, and it makes me wonder where are these people coming from?
<br />

<br />
Has SoE made twinking a bard and soloing/powerleveling to 60+ that easy?  Why do they choose bards?  A bard was /telling me for quite a while on how mad he was that they &quot;nerfed&quot; aoe kiting, and how he would make so much xp doing hoh, and how he quit his bard after that.  My question is, how did he even get to hoh?  
<br />

<br />
We have gone from a good group of people, a certain roleplayer type chose the bard from birth.  People who were entertainers, who were tact, who made people enjoy the group, back when bards had very little to offer besides level 32 manasong.  It seems this day even on higher end guilds in Time, a bard born late luclin can level their way up, use guilds and get to the top, only to give us a worse name.  Complaints of bards training, of not being able to twist and fight at the same time, of not knowing what songs stack for resists, or even what all the songs do, (had a bard ask me what nilipus's did at 65... ) what has this age come to?  
<br />

<br />
I have seen more and more bards turn from the good a bard can offer and seem to just go straight for loot and end game.  I urge you to earn it yourself, grow through the game yourself, don't rely on others to get you there.  And please don't be an immature player and use a bards ability to mess with spawns and trains and fights.
<br />

<br />
If you want to be an a$, be a wizard or cleric.</span></td>
