				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Has SoE made twinking a bard and soloing/powerleveling to 60+ that easy? </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Remove the word bard, and the answer is yes. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"> Why do they choose bards?</span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
Bards are, or were, the flavor of the month when you could get the aa and aoe kite for stupid huge amounts of exp.  First it was halfling dr00ds, then it was necros, now it's bards.  
<br />

<br />
For the PVP person, Bards were huge because they seemed to be the best (high resist, able to get and stay out of range, dots etc etc).  Then AE kiting made bards into the class of choice for the power gamer because we could get mad phat xps.  
<br />

<br />
I keep hoping it'll taper off, and I think it has to an extent, but all these d00ds are now realizing that bards are still powerful and great for solo and stuff, and they are in demand for guilds because bards were such a rare class.  
<br />

<br />
So, you've got all the power gamers that made bards and twinked/PL'd them so they could get the stupid amounts of exp by taking advantage of something SOE did wrong, and are staying because bards really are uber, which most peeps didn't realize for the longest time. 
<br />

<br />
What they don't get, and don't bother learning, was that part of why bards were uber is that they aren't as easy to play as the rest of the classes, and the only reason peeps stuck with the bard was because they liked the class and thereby knew how to play it.  
<br />

<br />
Since bards are in demand, and on a raid all they have to do is play resists, or mana, or whatever, they've never had to learn how to twist because even a poor bard is better than no bard for the raiders. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">A bard was /telling me for quite a while on how mad he was that they &quot;nerfed&quot; aoe kiting, and how he would make so much xp doing hoh, and how he quit his bard after that. My question is, how did he even get to hoh? </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
What the d00ds don't realize is that you can still AE kite if you are careful.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-14.gif" border="0" alt="Devil" hspace="2" /></span></td>
