				<td colspan="2"><span>Id have to agree, most higher guilds on my server have only like 3 bards max... though we have 4 time flagged guilds now, but still 2 - 3 bards in a time guild isnt that many considering a guild of about 100+ players. Im only bard in my guild at 65. It's hard to find &quot;good&quot; bard that know what they are doing these days.. esp when high end bards quit and give their account to a friend or something that doesnt know how or doesnt wanna learn how to play a bard, its rather sad. Some people just cant seem to get it down how to play... which is cool bards arent made for everyone... but i hate it when i hear of bards that play like one or 2 songs and thats it. I 99% of the time get complimented on my playing ability as a bard<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> .. i can mez, melee, twist other songs etc all at once... but it keeps me awake and its a rush $$. the other 1% of the times is when im uberly tired and can barely stay awake at keyboard and start to doze off behind the screen hehe =X. but yeah new charm roxxors and its fun swarm kiting hobs now =D... not greatest reg exp but hear its good AA... ummm.. mephits good exp and drop stuff most the time, theres a post in forum on how to get up on plateau ( it works i did it and dont have fading memories to go through the hobgob tunnel) charm a banshee or croc ... have it attack a gloom on plateau and when charm breaks it'll summon you up there.. so be prepared to get whacked a time or 2.. make sure your at least 75% health pending on hps... then kite away.. go to mephit cave.. charm one and kill off the glooms then do the cave =). bards are phat class if you know what you are doing... bottom line <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
