				<td colspan="2"><span>I am blessed I guess. 
<br />
My guild has about 100 members, but we never have enough on every night to fill a raid unless its a special night (Like when we keeled RZ WOOT).   
<br />
Out of those 100 members, we have 5 full time bards. All are full time bards, not PLd or twinked, we all played these same characters pre kunark. 
<br />
There are at least 3 of us on most nights, and a couple times a week we have all 5 on.  It is very nice when the raid leader has read through our portion of the guild website or takes our suggestions and places us in focused groups rather then making 10 little exp groups for the raid.  Wizards LOVE it when the group is 4 wizards, a Bard and a Druid.  Talk about a KS group!  And we are all very cool about loot and stuff.  The guild loot system is Award style, no points, so we kinda decide in bard channel who gets the special bard only stuff.  We try very hard to stay close to one another as far as gear goes, since we all play about the same time, we see ourselves as equals pretty much, and try to make sure the guild gets the best barding possible.  When we did KoS the second time, it was hilarious watching them decide who got the Crowned Staff of Anguish, it looked like those Gophers from the bugs bunny cartoons &quot;Why I insist you take take it&quot; , &quot;No, No, you certainly deserve it, I wouldnt think of taking it&quot;, &quot;I respect your opinion, thank you for your praise, but you contribute so much, please, take the staff&quot;....
<br />
Guild leader said &quot;Gratz Rot on staff&quot; and the rest of the guild called us all idiots before one of the other bards finally grabbed it (I had gotten the first one, Im not that polite lol)
<br />

<br />
I do agree that seeing some no skill, pl'd or swarmkiting bard with Elemental gear does make me feel a little envious and makes me doubt that guild's recruiting process.  But I am confident knowing that I provide my guild with the best barding possible.  And when I do exp or LDoN with guildmembers from &quot;Higher Teir&quot; guilds and get praise and wows from them, I am pretty confident that those swarmkiting bards are learning the hard way what it means to be a bard.
<br />
Its a game, people play it differently, i have fun playing it my way, I dont get my panties in a wad because some plays it another way</span></td>
